# Core Standards

## Scope

- Minimize diff scope. Solve the requested task only.
- Do not refactor unrelated code or add unrequested abstractions.
- Read neighboring files and match existing patterns before inventing new ones.

## Security

- Never commit `.env`, credentials, API keys, or secrets.
- Do not log sensitive data.

## Quality

- Run `npm run lint` after substantive code changes.
- Format with Prettier (`npm run format`) when touching many files.
- No test framework exists — do not add Jest, Vitest, or Playwright without approval.

## Git

- Do not create commits unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do not push to remote unless explicitly asked.

## Dependencies

- Do not add new npm packages unless required for the task.
- Prefer existing stack: Next.js, React, Tailwind v4, Chart.js.
